newsitem.title: AUSTRALIA: RTRS-Indonesia deal sparks Orbital shares.
newsitem.headline: RTRS-Indonesia deal sparks Orbital shares.

text.p: Shares in Australian engine designer Orbital Engine Corp Ltd rose nearly 10 percent on Friday after the company said its combustion process engine had been selected to power the planned Indonesia national car.
At 10.20 a.m. (0020 GMT), Orbital shares were 10 cents or 9.8 percent higher at A$1.12.

Orbital Engine said in an annoucement to the New York Stock Exchange on Thursday that it had been working with Indonesian government officals and the team for the so called Maleo project since mid-1995.
Orbital's ADR's ended on Thursday in New York at US$6-3/4, up 3/8.
